# ============================================================
# Tennis League Chatbot — Chat-to-Intent Server
# Manual test file (REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP Client)
#
# Prerequisites:
#   - Server running: uvicorn app.main:app --reload
#   - Replace {{league_id}} and {{host_token}} with real values
#     (or set them in an http-client.env.json / .env file)
# ============================================================

@baseUrl     = http://localhost:8000
@league_id   = d909cf3b-96b5-4ee2-b706-828b22dcbacf
@host_token  = 252b610f-2e68-4e72-b00c-ca2ab43d55be


# ============================================================
# HEALTH CHECK
# ============================================================

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health


# ============================================================
# READ INTENTS
# ============================================================

### GET_STANDINGS — "show me the standings"
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_message": "Show me the current standings",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### GET_STANDINGS — with host token (authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "What are the standings?",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### GET_ROSTER — "who's on the roster?"
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_message": "Who are the players in the league?",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### GET_MATCH_HISTORY — "show me past matches"
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_message": "Show me the match history",
  "last_server_message": ""
}


# ============================================================
# WRITE INTENTS
# (Server returns a prefilled payload for the frontend to submit.
#  The response includes data_type, data.method, data.url, data.body.)
# ============================================================

### SUBMIT_MATCH_RESULT — all info in one message
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Alice and Bob beat Charlie and Dave 6-3",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###


### SUBMIT_MATCH_RESULT — no info. Should still return the payload without default value
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Jae+Jazz 6:4 DK+Casper",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### SUBMIT_MATCH_RESULT — multi-turn: user provides score after clarification
# Step 1 — user sends incomplete message (no score)
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Alice and Bob vs Charlie and Dave",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

# Step 2 — user answers the clarification question
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "6-3",
  "last_server_message": "Who won, and what was the score?"
}

###

### EDIT_MATCH_SCORE — all info in one message
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Fix the score for Alice and Bob vs Charlie and Dave — it should be 6-4 not 6-3",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### EDIT_PLAYER_NICKNAME — rename a player
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Change Alice's nickname to Alicia",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### EDIT_PLAYER_NICKNAME — multi-turn: user provides new nickname after clarification
# Step 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "I want to rename Alice",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

# Step 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Alicia",
  "last_server_message": "What should the new nickname be?"
}

###

### DELETE_MATCH — identify match by four player nicknames
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Delete the match between Alice and Bob vs Charlie and Dave",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### DELETE_TEAM — identify team by both player nicknames
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json
X-Host-Token: {{host_token}}

{
  "client_message": "Remove the team Alice and Bob from the league",
  "last_server_message": ""
}


# ============================================================
# EDGE CASES
# ============================================================

### Ambiguous message — expect CLARIFICATION_QUESTION response
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_message": "help",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### Missing host token on a write intent — server still returns payload,
### but the downstream admin call will likely be rejected by the backend
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/{{league_id}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_message": "Alice and Bob beat Charlie and Dave 6-3",
  "last_server_message": ""
}

###

### Invalid league_id — backend will return 4xx, server wraps as 502 ERROR
POST {{baseUrl}}/leagues/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_message": "Show me the standings",
  "last_server_message": ""
}
